<TITLE> Over 50 tourists stranded on St Martin's </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Cox's Bazar, Oct 27 (bdnews24.com)Over 50 local and foreign tourists have been stranded on St Martin's Island in Cox's Bazar after shipping was suspended on Sunday due to rough seas. Jobaer Ahmed, a journalist currently on St Martin's Island, told bdnews24.com that 52 local and four foreign tourists were stranded at the popular tourist spot, as ship movement remained suspended for two days. The foreign holidaymakers include an Indian and a Spanish citizen staying at the Hotel Blue Marine, and two German tourists staying at the Shimana Periye Resort. Abu Noman, the manager of Cox's Bazar based passenger ferry Keari Sindbad, said no ships plied the Teknaf-St Martin's route on Sunday and Monday due to inclement weather. "The stranded tourists will be brought back when the sea calms down," said Noman. Chairman of St Martin's Union Parishad Maulana Feroz Ahmed said the stranded tourists are safe, and were receiving a 50 percent discount from their hotels. bdnewss24.
